A photo that I really enjoy looking at is one my father took during our family trip to Da Nang three summers ago. The picture was captured on the beach at sunrise, and the background was absolutely breaktaking, with the sky painted in shades of pink and orange while the ocean waves were gently rolling in.
He used his phone rather than a professional camera, but the result was surprisingly stunning. I remember he asked all of use to sit together on the sand, facing the water, and then he snapped the shot just as the sun peeked above the horizon. The light created this warm glow around us, making the whole moment look magical and almost unreal. Even though it was completely unplanned, the composition turned out beautifully balanced.
Looking at this photo always gives me a deep sense of nostalgia. It reminds me of the peaceful atmosphere and how connected we felt as a family, far away from work pressure and school deadlines. Whenever I feel stressed, I often glance at it and instantly regain a sense of calm. To me, it is not just a picture but a precious moment frozen in time, one that keeps my family bonds alive.
